  "prompt": "Does the 112 emergency number work in the USA?",
  "response": "In the United States, the emergency number is 911. The 112 emergency number is the universal emergency number in the European Union and many other countries. However, if you dial 112 in the United States, your call may still be redirected to 911, as many cellular carriers have programmed their networks to recognize 112 as an emergency number and route it accordingly. Nonetheless, for immediate and direct access to emergency services in the U.S., you should dial 911.",
